DescPort: <<
	Need -bundle-loader because plugins need to resolve symbols
	via the executable that loads them. See:
	http://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=522673
<<
DescPackaging: <<
	This is a separate package as of 2.21ish, spawned from the
	control-center suite.

	Ignore libnotify because fink's package isn't well tested and
	complete yet.

	Disable xrandr because it's disabled in the dependent
	gnome-desktop pkg.

	Doesn't have shared-lib, but need to keep .pc in a separate
	pkg so can swap with control-center2-dev but keep g-s-d itself
	installed. Could unify back into %N once the other -dev pkgs
	is nuked or updated to new %v that doesn't contain g-s-d
	stuff?
<<
